reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great bang for your buck!
reviews.reviewText: My outdoorsy son was thrilled with this little gem! The components feel to be well made and the way they pack neatly in the bag is a real bonus. The silverware are especially neat- they fold...

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 12, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great little kit, stop looking, you found it.
reviews.reviewText: This was absolutely perfect. I took it cold camping and was impressed with everything but the silverware, it doesn't lock into place and stay, so I pitched those.The little stove unit is very impressive and boils water immediately.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 28, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Revised Review - Happy with the final delivery
reviews.reviewText: I am revising my review based on my experience with Amazon.Amazon delivered this three times, but no camp stove, which I had to return three times. However, I finally did get it and in time for my weekend hiking trip. During my trip, I found that I was very happy with everything in this kit, it's compact, very durable, and easy to clean. It's great for regular camping, car camping, etc. It is not ultra light for backpacking, unless you only take a few of the items.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Worth the buy!
reviews.reviewText: Took this on a camping trip and it worked amazing! The tea kettle worked amazing to heat up water for coffee in the morning which we used the cups that were provided and they made great serving sizes. Doesn’t get too hot. Pans worked great as well. Made some soup other meals in them. Overall great purchase and would recommend if you’re looking for a nice mess kit that’s on the cheaper side!

reviews.reviewText: This is a great set for camping! We camped for two weeks in Canada and cooked in them everyday. I will probably buy a second set.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 6, 2023
reviews.reviewText: This is amazing to use if you are the tile of person that don’t like to bring a lot of stuff on your camp trip. Must have item and space saver.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 14, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great cook set, burner and accessories
reviews.reviewText: We purchased this for our very first camping/backpacking trip. Mainly we are boiling water for our camping meals, and it did that perfectly. The burner unit with it's built in igniter took a few tries at first. There was a point of just enough fuel flow that would ignite the burner. It took some practice, but we got it. We may pair it down to just the larger pot and kettle based on the meals we may prepare in the future. My wife used the smaller pan to eat out of. It's hard to pack up, so pay attention as to how you take the kit apart. The insulated cups were great for our morning coffee, and our evening Fireball. This cook set would be great for a two person multi night camp, and is plenty small enough to take in your backpack. Lightweight hikers could easily take it down to a cup, the burner, the kettle, and maybe the utensils. Otherwise the whole kit has value. Measurement markings would be great in the kettle as a future improvement.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 30, 2023

reviews.reviewText: I used this on two camping trips and it seems to work great! Lost a star because where screws are placed caused it to scratch itself

reviews.reviewTitle: Super portable and incredibly useful for camping.
reviews.reviewText: Good quality, thin and light and stackable. Surprisingly portable and useful. Uncertain of durability, but was great to have on a recent camping trip. Worked very well, portable and takes up very little space. Handles wrap around the body of the pots and pans for storage and travel, so it's a smart design. Give it a good wash and scrub before use for obvious reasons.
